description:
&lt;p&gt;We presently have Band 5 staff nurse vacancies for rotational posts at the Royal Alexandra Children&#39;s Hospital which would suit those newly registered. Please indicate in your supporting information those areas you would be interested in working and we will strive to accommodate requests wherever possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, professional nurses who want to make a real difference for the patients in our care. You should expect to be supported, supervised, challenged and mentored by our experienced staff. As a new staff member you will complete an orientation period to the clinical area and as a newly registered practitioner will have the opportunity to complete a Trust wide preceptorship programme with bespoke paediatric sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the Royal Alexandra Children’s Hospital we strive to prove the highest quality of medical and nursing care for all children and young people up to transition to adult services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Alexandra Children’s Hospital (RACH) has a history of progressive and innovative paediatric care embracing medicine, nursing and related professions, children’s nurse training and research. It is one of the leading children’s centres on the South East Coast for tertiary and general paediatrics in a variety of specialities: surgery, gastroenterology, diabetes, respiratory medicine, oncology care, day care services. We also have a busy 24-hour dedicated children’s Emergency Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Children’s services at the RACH has recently been deemed to be &#39;outstanding&#39; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is your opportunity to join the children’s nursing team at the Alex and continue to move our acute service forward. You will have support from a strong senior nursing team and a children’s practice education team for your ongoing learning and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our wards and departments are ideal environments to gain a variety of knowledge, skills and competence whether you are a newly registered nurse or a nurse with experience as we care for children with a wide variety of illnesses and conditions both acute and those that are more chronic or life long.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are proud to be able to offer a variety of flexible working options and contracts. For further information please refer to the Flexible Working for Registered Nurses document which is attached to this advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
